<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Aston Villa have agreed a £19million deal with Lyon for winger Bertrand Traore. </p>

<p>The club, who have also put a deal in place for Arsenal goalkeeper Emiliano Martinez, expect Traore to undergo a medical on Monday ahead of signing a three year contract. </p>

<p>The 25-year-old Traore played 35 matches last season, mainly on the right wing, and scored four goals, adding five assists. </p>

<p> Aston Villa have agreed a £19million deal with French club Lyon to sign winger Bertrand Traore</p>

<p>He wants to leave though after finding himself frozen out of their Champions League finish and spending more time on the bench. </p>

<p>Villa remain discussions with Werder Bremen also over an £18m deal for attacking midfielder Milot Rashica.</p>

<p>Rashica, 24, is a priority for boss Dean Smith - and is likely to leave the Bundesliga club during this window, having asked for a move last month.  </p>

<p>The club expect Traore to undergo a medical on Monday ahead of signing a three year deal</p>
